<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-04T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-04T05:00:00-05:00" n="510" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d510">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">560.AL/10–447: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Troutman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-04T11:00:00+01:00">October 4,
                                1947—11 a.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1078. <gloss target="#t_Frito1">Frito</gloss> 233. For Wilcox from Brown.
                        Have reached tentative agreement Helmore recommendations to be considered by
                        Cripps and <gloss target="#t_TAC1">TAC</gloss> over weekend. Will report in
                            detail.<note n="1" xml:id="d510fn1">This detailed information was sent
                            in telegram 1077 from Geneva, October 4, not printed.</note> These
                        recommendations <pb facs="1037" n="1007" xml:id="pg_1007"/> incorporate all
                        suggestions <gloss target="#t_Toito1">Toito</gloss> 243 except (4). Canadian
                        negotiating teams at work and hope have recommendations <gloss target="#t_TAC1">TAC</gloss> by middle next week. Will see Coombs today
                        on important issues still unresolved with Australia.</p>
                    <p>Sent Dept; repeated London as 128 for Hawkins. [Brown.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Troutman</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>